property.name: note
property.value:
We always begin in low-intensity peril, but we can set a switch to go to high intensity peril at any point. (We cannot return to low-intensity peril at this time from high-intensity peril.) At any point we can trigger any of the three endings, "END A" "END B" or "END C".
END A: A moderately ominious, final-sounding thing. The most "whew, got away with that" of the bunch.
END B: A sudden, abrupt stop, followed by a sinister downfall idea, suitable for being arrested, or thrown out, or whatnot, something with lingering consequences.
END C: An abrupt and curt little thing, that lends itself to surprise.
